{
  "children": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Understanding the Fourier Transform"
        }
      ],
      "level": 1,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "The "
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Fourier Transform"
            }
          ],
          "type": "bold"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " decomposes a function into its constituent frequencies. It is fundamental to signal processing, image compression, and quantum mechanics."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Definition"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "The continuous Fourier Transform of a function "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "f(t)"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " is defined as:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "body": "F(\\omega) = \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} f(t) e^{-i\\omega t} \\, dt",
      "type": "math_block"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "And the inverse transform is:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "body": "f(t) = \\frac{1}{2\\pi} \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} F(\\omega) e^{i\\omega t} \\, d\\omega",
      "type": "math_block"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Key Properties"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "items": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "Linearity"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "bold"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": ": "
                },
                {
                  "type": "inline_math",
                  "value": "\\mathcal{F}[af + bg] = a\\mathcal{F}[f] + b\\mathcal{F}[g]"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "Time Shifting"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "bold"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": ": If "
                },
                {
                  "type": "inline_math",
                  "value": "f(t) \\to F(\\omega)"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": ", then "
                },
                {
                  "type": "inline_math",
                  "value": "f(t - t_0) \\to e^{-i\\omega t_0} F(\\omega)"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "Convolution Theorem"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "bold"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": ": "
                },
                {
                  "type": "inline_math",
                  "value": "\\mathcal{F}[f * g] = F(\\omega) \\cdot G(\\omega)"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "start": 1,
      "type": "ordered_list"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Discrete Fourier Transform"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "For a sequence of "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "N"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " samples, the DFT is:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "body": "X_k = \\sum_{n=0}^{N-1} x_n \\cdot e^{-i 2\\pi k n / N}",
      "type": "math_block"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "The "
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Fast Fourier Transform"
            }
          ],
          "type": "bold"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " (FFT) computes the DFT in "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "O(N \\log N)"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " time instead of "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "O(N^2)"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Python Example"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "body": "import numpy as np\n\n# Generate a signal with two frequencies\nt = np.linspace(0, 1, 1000)\nsignal = np.sin(2 * np.pi * 50 * t) + 0.5 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * 120 * t)\n\n# Compute FFT\nfft_result = np.fft.fft(signal)\nfrequencies = np.fft.fftfreq(len(signal), d=t[1] - t[0])",
      "lang": "python",
      "type": "code_block"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "The FFT is one of the most important algorithms in computational science. It enables real-time audio processing, medical imaging, and telecommunications."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "foldable": false,
      "kind": "note",
      "type": "admonition"
    }
  ]
}